text: Däniken is a municipality in the Olten district in the canton of Solothurn in Switzerland. Rich people live in the upper half of Däniken. Others live in the lower half. That half has a nuclear power plant. Its name is Gösgen. Däniken has a lot of industry. == References == == Other websites == * Official website Municipalities of Solothurn
title: Däniken, Solothurn
